# SCRUM-571 (Wave 8): artifacts moved out of the engine dir to the data dir
# `.ai-specs/changes/`. The full trail — plans, records, verify AND state — is
# COMMITTED there (operator's state-committed knob; completes the audit trail
# and fixes the Wave-6 class of bug where gitignored state broke CI). So NO
# ignore rule for `.ai-specs/` or for state files. (The old blanket `.ai-specs/`
# ignore was a dead leftover of the deleted Phase-3 orchestrator-session.)

# Python bytecode (generated by py_compile)
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Post W64 SCRUM-632: legacy orchestrator/ checkpoint + strategy-session
# locations (pre-relocation paths; the relocated checkpointers write to
# framework/_runtime/orchestrator/.checkpoints/ and .strategy-sessions/
# instead). Per ADR-015 §Consequences these legacy paths are abandoned but
# retained on PRIVATE; git should not stage them.
orchestrator/.checkpoints/
orchestrator/.strategy-sessions/
